1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:36,550 --> 00:01:41,009
[Strange Tales of Tang Dynasty II To the West]

3
00:01:41,930 --> 00:01:43,979
[Episode 13]

4
00:02:17,230 --> 00:02:18,490
Which way should we go?

5
00:02:18,760 --> 00:02:20,490
Let the horses rest for a while.

6
00:02:21,880 --> 00:02:22,870
Fed

7
00:02:22,890 --> 00:02:24,130
left in the middle of the night.

8
00:02:24,130 --> 00:02:25,930
He said he would be the vanguard.

9
00:02:25,930 --> 00:02:27,040
I wonder which way

10
00:02:27,070 --> 00:02:27,870
he went first.

11
00:02:28,750 --> 00:02:29,810
Chicken Fed

12
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:32,420
is just the vanguard who scouts for alcohol.

13
00:02:32,540 --> 00:02:34,200
No matter where he gets drunk,

14
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:35,079
in a few days,

15
00:02:35,270 --> 00:02:36,620
he'll catch up with us.

16
00:02:36,790 --> 00:02:38,920
That must be because he's out of money.

17
00:02:44,760 --> 00:02:46,500
[Longyou-Hexi Map]

18
00:02:51,030 --> 00:02:52,630
It's about ten miles

19
00:02:53,190 --> 00:02:54,790
from the last stage station.

20
00:02:55,870 --> 00:02:58,270
How come there's no stage station in sight?

21
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:10,750
Sir.

22
00:03:11,190 --> 00:03:12,000
May I ask

23
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:14,160
if there's a stage station ahead?

24
00:03:19,820 --> 00:03:21,540
Maybe it's because he's old.

25
00:03:21,750 --> 00:03:22,950
He's hard of hearing.

26
00:03:24,510 --> 00:03:25,150
Sir.

27
00:03:25,350 --> 00:03:26,340
It's freezing.

28
00:03:26,550 --> 00:03:27,770
You're wearing thin clothes.

29
00:03:27,770 --> 00:03:30,030
How about giving you an item of clothing?

30
00:03:33,620 --> 00:03:34,420
Bring it to me.

31
00:03:37,230 --> 00:03:38,030
Are you

32
00:03:38,310 --> 00:03:39,770
giving him clothes or not?

33
00:03:40,630 --> 00:03:41,270
Yes, I am.

34
00:03:47,270 --> 00:03:47,870
Sir.

35
00:03:51,590 --> 00:03:52,440
May I ask

36
00:03:52,740 --> 00:03:55,270
if there's a place to rest from where you came?

37
00:03:55,780 --> 00:03:56,350
No.

38
00:03:58,310 --> 00:03:59,850
Then is there a village?

39
00:04:00,990 --> 00:04:01,630
No.

40
00:04:02,790 --> 00:04:05,120
Then where did you come from?

41
00:04:05,990 --> 00:04:07,070
What's it to you?

42
00:04:07,500 --> 00:04:08,260
Old man.

43
00:04:08,350 --> 00:04:09,210
How rude of you.

44
00:04:10,790 --> 00:04:11,550
Don't stop me.

45
00:04:11,550 --> 00:04:12,520
Let me teach him a lesson.

46
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:13,050
Forget it.

47
00:04:13,050 --> 00:04:14,010
He's old.

48
00:04:14,100 --> 00:04:15,070
The world is vast.

49
00:04:15,070 --> 00:04:16,240
Jianghu is a mixed bag.

50
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:17,560
Although this man is old,

51
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:19,089
he may not have a good heart.

52
00:04:19,230 --> 00:04:20,589
We kindly gave you clothes,

53
00:04:20,589 --> 00:04:21,750
but you responded coldly.

54
00:04:21,750 --> 00:04:23,310
You even refused to give us directions when we asked you.

55
00:04:23,310 --> 00:04:24,310
It makes no sense.

56
00:04:26,230 --> 00:04:27,070
I said,

57
00:04:28,030 --> 00:04:28,430
"No."

58
00:04:28,670 --> 00:04:29,070
You...

59
00:04:31,030 --> 00:04:32,360
If we take the main road,

60
00:04:32,390 --> 00:04:34,230
the next stage station

61
00:04:34,360 --> 00:04:35,870
will be dozens of miles from here.

62
00:04:35,870 --> 00:04:37,550
Taking the path is a bit quicker.

63
00:04:37,550 --> 00:04:39,400
But I don't know if the path

64
00:04:39,430 --> 00:04:40,350
is easy to go.

65
00:04:40,990 --> 00:04:41,870
No, it isn't.

66
00:04:42,940 --> 00:04:44,960
There're snow pits ahead.

67
00:04:45,260 --> 00:04:47,790
The weather is cold, and the path is slippery.

68
00:04:48,060 --> 00:04:50,020
It's likely that you'll fall and die.

69
00:04:50,020 --> 00:04:50,560
You...

70
00:04:51,310 --> 00:04:51,990
Yingtao.

71
00:04:52,390 --> 00:04:53,050
Put it down.

72
00:04:54,230 --> 00:04:54,990
Put it away.

73
00:05:09,830 --> 00:05:10,430
Yingtao.

74
00:05:10,830 --> 00:05:11,980
No offence.

75
00:05:12,070 --> 00:05:13,070
Your temper...

76
00:05:28,190 --> 00:05:30,660
[Turn a Robber into a Buddha]

77
00:05:32,710 --> 00:05:33,600
Guess

78
00:05:33,630 --> 00:05:34,950
what these words are.

79
00:05:38,060 --> 00:05:39,590
Become a Buddha on the Spot?

80
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:44,470
See the Nature and Become a Buddha?

81
00:05:51,750 --> 00:05:52,940
Let's take the path.

82
00:05:53,550 --> 00:05:56,070
There should be a temple ahead.

83
00:05:56,180 --> 00:06:00,110
[Mo's Inn in a Snowstorm]

84
00:06:11,990 --> 00:06:12,830
We just saw

85
00:06:12,870 --> 00:06:15,220
a large area of wild green onions and chives.

86
00:06:15,220 --> 00:06:16,310
Why did it begin to snow so heavily

87
00:06:16,310 --> 00:06:17,590
all of a sudden?

88
00:06:18,510 --> 00:06:19,510
Didn't the old man

89
00:06:19,550 --> 00:06:20,750
riding the donkey say

90
00:06:20,910 --> 00:06:22,310
that there're snow pits?

91
00:06:22,490 --> 00:06:24,270
But it's early winter now.

92
00:06:24,610 --> 00:06:27,130
The journey to the west is quite cold.

93
00:06:27,390 --> 00:06:28,820
If we pass the frontier,

94
00:06:28,940 --> 00:06:30,480
snow in August

95
00:06:30,510 --> 00:06:31,680
won't be strange either.

96
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:32,420
Su Wuming.

97
00:06:32,830 --> 00:06:33,780
Where is the temple

98
00:06:33,780 --> 00:06:34,750
you mentioned?

99
00:06:35,490 --> 00:06:37,010
It should be right ahead.

100
00:06:51,230 --> 00:06:51,790
Brother.

101
00:06:52,100 --> 00:06:53,190
There's no temple.

102
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:54,600
But there's an inn.

103
00:06:55,830 --> 00:06:56,990
Mo's Inn?

104
00:06:57,950 --> 00:06:58,430
Let's go

105
00:06:58,610 --> 00:06:59,190
and have a look.

106
00:06:59,190 --> 00:06:59,670
Wait.

107
00:07:00,880 --> 00:07:02,210
Let's walk a bit further

108
00:07:02,570 --> 00:07:04,150
and stay at an official stage station.

109
00:07:04,150 --> 00:07:06,250
But it's dozens of miles away.

110
00:07:06,670 --> 00:07:07,410
But this place

111
00:07:07,410 --> 00:07:08,590
looks really weird.

112
00:07:08,420 --> 00:07:14,340
[Mo's Inn]

113
00:07:08,830 --> 00:07:10,030
Generally speaking,

114
00:07:10,030 --> 00:07:10,910
private inns

115
00:07:10,930 --> 00:07:11,900
should be built on a roadside

116
00:07:11,900 --> 00:07:13,490
to attract passing travelers.

117
00:07:13,490 --> 00:07:14,620
But look at this inn.

118
00:07:14,710 --> 00:07:15,480
It's built

119
00:07:15,510 --> 00:07:16,710
deep in a remote area.

120
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:20,020
This inn isn't only weird.

121
00:07:20,970 --> 00:07:22,630
It may also have some history.

122
00:07:23,390 --> 00:07:25,030
I don't know if it has a history.

123
00:07:25,030 --> 00:07:25,960
But I'm

124
00:07:25,990 --> 00:07:27,040
really hungry.

125
00:07:27,190 --> 00:07:27,920
Lu Lingfeng.

126
00:07:28,330 --> 00:07:29,190
Why did you become so cautious

127
00:07:29,190 --> 00:07:30,180
all of a sudden?

128
00:07:30,950 --> 00:07:32,290
I'm going to Yunding to take office.

129
00:07:32,290 --> 00:07:33,750
You're going west with me.

130
00:07:33,790 --> 00:07:35,270
With responsibility on my shoulders,

131
00:07:35,270 --> 00:07:36,730
I don't want any mistakes.

132
00:07:37,030 --> 00:07:38,360
Let's walk a bit further

133
00:07:38,540 --> 00:07:40,540
and find an official stage station.

134
00:07:43,980 --> 00:07:45,909
It's no use for you two to look at me.

135
00:07:46,310 --> 00:07:48,909
We all have to listen to Sheriff Lu.

136
00:07:48,990 --> 00:07:49,700
Stop right there!

137
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:50,630
You can't leave!

138
00:07:50,790 --> 00:07:52,020
You ate two chickens

139
00:07:52,070 --> 00:07:53,380
but only paid for one.

140
00:07:53,670 --> 00:07:54,670
You can't go.

141
00:07:55,070 --> 00:07:55,900
Chicken Fed.

142
00:07:58,630 --> 00:07:59,360
Lu Lingfeng.

143
00:07:59,750 --> 00:08:02,010
Whether to stay or not isn't up to you now.

144
00:08:03,300 --> 00:08:03,830
Let's go.

145
00:08:05,050 --> 00:08:06,030
Let me ask you.

146
00:08:06,340 --> 00:08:08,200
How many legs does a chicken have?

147
00:08:08,870 --> 00:08:09,490
Two.

148
00:08:09,710 --> 00:08:11,070
Say it with confidence.

149
00:08:11,970 --> 00:08:13,740
[The Old Waiter of the Mo's Inn]

150
00:08:12,570 --> 00:08:13,130
Two.

151
00:08:13,310 --> 00:08:14,700
Right. Definitely two.

152
00:08:14,730 --> 00:08:16,930
Then how many legs do two chickens have?

153
00:08:17,820 --> 00:08:19,320
Four... Four legs.

154
00:08:19,350 --> 00:08:20,430
That's correct.

155
00:08:20,920 --> 00:08:22,220
When I ate chicken,

156
00:08:22,350 --> 00:08:24,560
I only ate two legs.

157
00:08:24,590 --> 00:08:26,230
If I can't pay for one chicken,

158
00:08:26,230 --> 00:08:27,690
how much more should I pay?

159
00:08:28,700 --> 00:08:30,100
It can't be just two legs.

160
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:31,500
You're cheating.

161
00:08:31,790 --> 00:08:32,750
I... I...

162
00:08:36,350 --> 00:08:37,710
You... What are you going to do?

163
00:08:37,710 --> 00:08:38,549
What am I going to do?

164
00:08:38,549 --> 00:08:39,950
I'm beating you to death!

165
00:08:42,309 --> 00:08:43,510
How dare you run! I...

166
00:08:46,370 --> 00:08:47,430
What are you doing?

167
00:08:51,580 --> 00:08:54,530
[Lady of Mo's Inn]

168
00:08:53,510 --> 00:08:54,880
Why are you slacking again?

169
00:08:54,880 --> 00:08:55,950
He cheated!

170
00:08:56,350 --> 00:08:57,180
Who cheated?

171
00:08:58,030 --> 00:08:58,710
Landlady.

172
00:08:59,110 --> 00:09:00,110
If you don't believe me,

173
00:09:00,110 --> 00:09:01,350
you can count the chicken bones

174
00:09:01,350 --> 00:09:02,450
I ate

175
00:09:02,670 --> 00:09:04,470
and see how many legs there were.

176
00:09:04,550 --> 00:09:05,950
You go back inside first.

177
00:09:13,230 --> 00:09:15,870
Landlady, you're more sensible.

178
00:09:16,670 --> 00:09:18,390
Why don't you leave after taking advantage?

179
00:09:18,390 --> 00:09:20,030
Aren't you afraid that I'll get angry

180
00:09:20,030 --> 00:09:21,470
and stew you together with chickens?

181
00:09:21,470 --> 00:09:22,910
I do have two legs.

182
00:09:23,550 --> 00:09:25,310
But I don't have wings.

183
00:09:26,070 --> 00:09:26,630
Besides,

184
00:09:26,900 --> 00:09:28,160
does the pot in your inn

185
00:09:28,230 --> 00:09:30,190
big enough to stew me?

186
00:09:32,910 --> 00:09:33,870
Get lost.

187
00:09:36,150 --> 00:09:37,830
I forgive you.

188
00:09:41,190 --> 00:09:44,940
♫If you ask what the happiest thing in the world is♫

189
00:09:45,790 --> 00:09:49,630
♫It's to eat and drink as I please♫

190
00:09:57,790 --> 00:09:58,350
You...

191
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:00,790
You...

192
00:10:00,970 --> 00:10:01,900
You finally said

193
00:10:01,900 --> 00:10:03,270
your life ambition.

194
00:10:05,630 --> 00:10:07,110
You also took the path?

195
00:10:07,550 --> 00:10:09,310
There's a big slope on the path.

196
00:10:11,310 --> 00:10:12,660
Judging from your appearance,

197
00:10:12,660 --> 00:10:13,990
I guess you didn't fall.

198
00:10:14,430 --> 00:10:15,030
Uncle Fed.

199
00:10:15,150 --> 00:10:16,050
Who hit you?

200
00:10:16,630 --> 00:10:18,030
Is it the waiter just now?

201
00:10:18,170 --> 00:10:19,360
Let me teach him a lesson for you.

202
00:10:19,360 --> 00:10:20,290
No need. No need.

203
00:10:20,510 --> 00:10:21,590
Didn't I just say

204
00:10:21,670 --> 00:10:23,150
that there's a big slope?

205
00:10:23,900 --> 00:10:25,710
The snow was heavy, and the road was slippery.

206
00:10:25,710 --> 00:10:28,030
My horse and I slipped and fell.

207
00:10:28,140 --> 00:10:30,330
The horse fell into a deep ditch.

208
00:10:30,350 --> 00:10:31,480
It took me a long time

209
00:10:31,500 --> 00:10:32,620
to climb up.

210
00:10:32,670 --> 00:10:33,800
Then it became like this.

211
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:34,520
Brother is

212
00:10:34,550 --> 00:10:36,360
well-traveled and knowledgeable.

213
00:10:36,360 --> 00:10:37,240
Seeing the snow was heavy,

214
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:39,030
he asked us to dismount and lead the horses.

215
00:10:39,030 --> 00:10:40,700
The deep ditch you mentioned

216
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:42,580
may be caused by ground fissures.

217
00:10:42,750 --> 00:10:44,740
Some of the deep ditches in the mountains

218
00:10:44,740 --> 00:10:46,340
are hundreds of meters deep.

219
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:47,670
It's good that you're fine.

220
00:10:47,670 --> 00:10:49,030
I'm very hard to kill.

221
00:10:49,150 --> 00:10:50,820
God doesn't want me.

222
00:10:51,230 --> 00:10:52,060
Let's go back

223
00:10:52,540 --> 00:10:53,550
and take the main road.

224
00:10:53,550 --> 00:10:54,240
Let's go.

225
00:10:54,950 --> 00:10:56,550
You're full.

226
00:10:56,710 --> 00:10:57,990
But we're still hungry.

227
00:10:57,990 --> 00:10:58,510
Fed.

228
00:10:58,970 --> 00:10:59,990
Why are you in such a hurry

229
00:10:59,990 --> 00:11:00,710
to leave?

230
00:11:04,710 --> 00:11:06,170
Their inn is strange.

231
00:11:06,430 --> 00:11:08,190
I can't say what's strange about it.

232
00:11:08,190 --> 00:11:09,070
It's just strange.

233
00:11:09,070 --> 00:11:10,350
The Mo's Inn looks

234
00:11:10,370 --> 00:11:11,400
quite new.

235
00:11:11,430 --> 00:11:13,510
It doesn't seem like an old haunted inn.

236
00:11:13,510 --> 00:11:15,500
Besides, the snow is too heavy.

237
00:11:16,630 --> 00:11:17,940
Why don't we stay here?

238
00:11:19,070 --> 00:11:19,790
But this place...

239
00:11:19,790 --> 00:11:20,310
What?

240
00:11:20,590 --> 00:11:22,510
You don't dare to stay

241
00:11:22,530 --> 00:11:23,950
at this remote inn?

242
00:11:24,670 --> 00:11:26,830
If Liu Shiba knew it,

243
00:11:26,870 --> 00:11:28,670
he would definitely laugh at us.

244
00:11:28,700 --> 00:11:29,870
Who is Liu Shiba?

245
00:11:32,390 --> 00:11:33,250
I remember now.

246
00:11:33,470 --> 00:11:34,470
You told me before

247
00:11:34,590 --> 00:11:36,910
about the Gantang Post.

248
00:11:38,870 --> 00:11:39,510
This place

249
00:11:39,730 --> 00:11:42,230
is even weirder than the Gantang Post.

250
00:11:45,590 --> 00:11:46,230
I...

251
00:11:50,950 --> 00:11:52,550
You're really staying here?

252
00:11:53,020 --> 00:11:53,980
It's weird.

253
00:11:54,780 --> 00:11:57,630
I'm not in a hurry to take office in Yunding.

254
00:11:57,990 --> 00:12:00,030
Encounter something weird on the way and get to the bottom of it.

255
00:12:00,030 --> 00:12:01,110
Isn't it a joy?

256
00:12:02,350 --> 00:12:03,350
Su Wuming, so you're

257
00:12:03,350 --> 00:12:04,480
doing this for fun?

258
00:12:04,520 --> 00:12:06,380
You're even less serious than me.

259
00:12:07,700 --> 00:12:08,590
Let's go.

260
00:12:21,390 --> 00:12:21,990
Landlady.

261
00:12:23,010 --> 00:12:24,780
The five of us would like to stay at the inn.

262
00:12:24,780 --> 00:12:28,420
[Good Fortune Throughout the Year]

263
00:12:25,020 --> 00:12:26,270
My Mo's Inn

264
00:12:26,530 --> 00:12:29,030
isn't a place where ordinary people can stay.

265
00:12:29,030 --> 00:12:30,700
If you want to go in and rest,

266
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:32,100
each one of you

267
00:12:32,540 --> 00:12:34,400
needs to show your unique skills.

268
00:12:35,430 --> 00:12:36,690
What kind of rule is it?

269
00:12:36,990 --> 00:12:38,110
It's my inn.

270
00:12:38,480 --> 00:12:40,390
I made the rule.

271
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:42,030
Fed.

272
00:12:43,190 --> 00:12:45,390
What unique skill did you show just now?

273
00:12:45,990 --> 00:12:47,760
There was no such rule just now.

274
00:12:48,030 --> 00:12:48,830
He's right.

275
00:12:49,070 --> 00:12:49,750
The rule

276
00:12:50,060 --> 00:12:51,030
was just made.

277
00:12:51,710 --> 00:12:52,390
What?

278
00:12:52,950 --> 00:12:54,810
You don't even want to make money?

279
00:12:54,830 --> 00:12:56,790
There're already guests at my inn.

280
00:12:56,910 --> 00:12:58,030
You're quite a few.

281
00:12:58,350 --> 00:12:59,550
If you all stay

282
00:12:59,890 --> 00:13:01,950
and the heavy snow continues for a few more days,

283
00:13:01,950 --> 00:13:02,990
the food at my inn

284
00:13:02,990 --> 00:13:04,230
may not be enough.

285
00:13:04,550 --> 00:13:05,270
Then I'll have to go to

286
00:13:05,270 --> 00:13:07,400
the town dozens of miles away to buy it.

287
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:08,620
The weather is so cold.

288
00:13:08,620 --> 00:13:09,790
I don't want to bother.

289
00:13:09,790 --> 00:13:11,300
Then let's just keep going.

290
00:13:11,300 --> 00:13:12,310
Keep going. Keep going.

291
00:13:12,310 --> 00:13:12,950
I must stay

292
00:13:13,710 --> 00:13:14,790
at this inn.

293
00:13:15,270 --> 00:13:17,390
