580
00:25:07,070 --> 00:25:07,800
Please go in.

581
00:25:09,630 --> 00:25:10,890
Unique skills, right?

582
00:25:11,870 --> 00:25:12,470
Don't mind

583
00:25:13,230 --> 00:25:14,430
if I do.

584
00:25:16,030 --> 00:25:17,760
You really have a unique skill?

585
00:25:18,230 --> 00:25:19,830
Guys, come and see!

586
00:25:20,100 --> 00:25:21,540
There's a unique skill!

587
00:25:21,590 --> 00:25:23,750
Come out quickly and see it!

588
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:24,850
-Let's go.
-Hurry up!

589
00:25:24,850 --> 00:25:25,660
Let's go and see.

590
00:25:25,660 --> 00:25:26,250
Okay.

591
00:25:26,950 --> 00:25:27,480
Let's go.

592
00:25:27,710 --> 00:25:28,710
Let's take a look.

593
00:25:42,490 --> 00:25:44,880
[Swordsman]

594
00:27:07,510 --> 00:27:09,110
I just performed an illusion

595
00:27:10,230 --> 00:27:10,990
to climb a lofty mountain

596
00:27:10,990 --> 00:27:12,520
of the Eastern Jin Dynasty.

597
00:27:12,920 --> 00:27:13,920
My feet were sore.

598
00:27:14,590 --> 00:27:15,720
While I was resting,

599
00:27:15,870 --> 00:27:17,790
I saw someone coming with a goose cage on his back.

600
00:27:17,790 --> 00:27:19,420
I wanted to borrow the goose cage to rest.

601
00:27:19,420 --> 00:27:21,470
But then I thought I still needed to stay here,

602
00:27:21,470 --> 00:27:22,270
so I came back.

603
00:27:23,270 --> 00:27:24,670
A scholar from Yangxian?

604
00:27:26,870 --> 00:27:28,240
In that case,

605
00:27:28,340 --> 00:27:29,660
we don't need to bother

606
00:27:29,680 --> 00:27:30,810
Landlady tonight.

607
00:27:30,910 --> 00:27:32,830
Let's ask Hermit Jiang

608
00:27:32,850 --> 00:27:34,590
to make some fine alcohol and delicacies

609
00:27:34,590 --> 00:27:36,470
for us to enjoy.

610
00:27:36,830 --> 00:27:37,690
It would be best

611
00:27:37,780 --> 00:27:39,260
if you could make a beauty

612
00:27:39,610 --> 00:27:40,680
to drink

613
00:27:40,710 --> 00:27:41,690
with my friend.

614
00:27:42,730 --> 00:27:43,970
Good. Good.

615
00:27:44,390 --> 00:27:46,780
Although I learnt some illusion skills,

616
00:27:47,590 --> 00:27:48,940
I can't make

617
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:50,270
fine alcohol and delicacies.

618
00:27:50,270 --> 00:27:50,670
I

619
00:27:51,030 --> 00:27:51,990
can't make a person either.

620
00:27:51,990 --> 00:27:53,720
He got our hopes up for nothing.

621
00:27:54,070 --> 00:27:54,950
This...

622
00:27:55,390 --> 00:27:56,910
In front of so many scholars,

623
00:27:56,910 --> 00:27:58,110
I showed off my skill.

624
00:27:58,470 --> 00:27:59,530
Please don't mind.

625
00:28:03,100 --> 00:28:03,640
Xijun.

626
00:28:04,110 --> 00:28:05,250
Which book is this?

627
00:28:05,470 --> 00:28:06,930
I've never read it before.

628
00:28:07,790 --> 00:28:08,960
It's a mystery tale.

629
00:28:08,990 --> 00:28:10,390
I'll tell you this later.

630
00:28:10,870 --> 00:28:11,510
Hermit.

631
00:28:11,780 --> 00:28:13,110
Don't stand in the snow.

632
00:28:13,190 --> 00:28:14,020
Come in.

633
00:28:14,640 --> 00:28:15,840
Thank you, Landlady.

634
00:28:15,910 --> 00:28:16,370
Please.

635
00:28:37,060 --> 00:28:37,720
You've been

636
00:28:38,190 --> 00:28:40,920
running this inn for seven or eight years, right?

637
00:28:42,480 --> 00:28:43,190
I mean

638
00:28:43,910 --> 00:28:46,510
you should have some vintage alcohol in stock.

639
00:28:47,510 --> 00:28:48,200
Of course.

640
00:28:48,470 --> 00:28:49,030
Good eye.

641
00:28:49,750 --> 00:28:52,350
I've been running this inn for about ten years.

642
00:28:52,440 --> 00:28:54,300
Of course I have vintage alcohol.

643
00:28:55,190 --> 00:28:55,990
Serve dishes.

644
00:28:57,500 --> 00:28:58,510
I'm in no rush to eat dishes.

645
00:28:58,510 --> 00:28:59,110
Alcohol.

646
00:28:59,420 --> 00:29:00,750
The sooner, the better.

647
00:29:00,870 --> 00:29:02,000
I'd like to get warm.

648
00:29:02,110 --> 00:29:02,750
Okay.

649
00:29:04,590 --> 00:29:06,430
Hurry up and serve our alcohol too.

650
00:29:06,430 --> 00:29:07,910
Serve it together with the dishes.

651
00:29:07,910 --> 00:29:09,070
Also, when serving the chicken,

652
00:29:09,070 --> 00:29:10,200
count how many legs it has.

653
00:29:10,200 --> 00:29:12,660
Don't accuse me of not paying the bill later.

654
00:29:24,650 --> 00:29:26,250
Why are you two looking at me?

655
00:29:49,750 --> 00:29:50,350
Mr. Jiang.

656
00:29:51,430 --> 00:29:53,150
I saw your impressive illusion skill just now.

657
00:29:53,150 --> 00:29:53,820
You even showed us

658
00:29:53,820 --> 00:29:55,390
the essence of scholars in Yangxian.

659
00:29:55,390 --> 00:29:56,590
It was truly amazing.

660
00:29:57,030 --> 00:29:58,350
Since we met at this remote inn

661
00:29:58,350 --> 00:29:59,830
on this snowy night,

662
00:30:00,190 --> 00:30:02,310
would you like to join us for a drink?

663
00:30:03,540 --> 00:30:04,360
Well said.

664
00:30:03,810 --> 00:30:06,120
[Lan Juzi]

665
00:30:04,690 --> 00:30:06,150
Fate brought us together.

666
00:30:06,230 --> 00:30:06,710
Come.

667
00:30:07,750 --> 00:30:09,350
I'll join you for a drink too.

668
00:30:14,540 --> 00:30:15,310
It's good to drink together.

669
00:30:14,780 --> 00:30:16,590
[Jia Buli]

670
00:30:15,910 --> 00:30:16,930
It's good to drink together.

671
00:30:16,930 --> 00:30:19,060
I just finished my alcohol over there.

672
00:30:19,190 --> 00:30:19,630
Mi.

673
00:30:19,840 --> 00:30:20,640
Come quickly.

674
00:30:20,750 --> 00:30:22,020
Let's sit

675
00:30:23,310 --> 00:30:24,440
and drink together.

676
00:30:30,110 --> 00:30:31,110
Put your bag down.

677
00:30:31,420 --> 00:30:32,950
Who would steal it from you?

678
00:30:32,950 --> 00:30:33,750
No, I can't.

679
00:30:34,180 --> 00:30:35,480
This bag of stuff

680
00:30:35,770 --> 00:30:37,870
is worth more than ten years of salaries you'll receive as an imperial scholar

681
00:30:37,870 --> 00:30:39,910
after you pass the imperial examination.

682
00:30:39,910 --> 00:30:40,810
I can't put it down.

683
00:30:40,810 --> 00:30:41,670
Stop bragging.

684
00:30:41,940 --> 00:30:42,990
Right.

685
00:30:43,110 --> 00:30:44,240
I was just bragging.

686
00:30:45,020 --> 00:30:45,550
Look.

687
00:30:46,030 --> 00:30:47,570
You're being taken advantage of.

688
00:30:47,570 --> 00:30:48,590
In the future, in places like this,

689
00:30:48,590 --> 00:30:50,390
you can't pretend to be rich.

690
00:30:50,740 --> 00:30:51,640
You...

691
00:30:57,510 --> 00:30:58,970
Thanks for your kindness.

692
00:31:00,110 --> 00:31:01,740
Your reserve

693
00:31:02,540 --> 00:31:04,230
cost him a lot of money.

694
00:31:05,260 --> 00:31:05,990
Don't worry.

695
00:31:06,430 --> 00:31:08,560
This man has graces.

696
00:31:08,780 --> 00:31:09,510
He's obviously

697
00:31:09,510 --> 00:31:10,540
a rich man.

698
00:31:13,950 --> 00:31:15,080
That man over there.

699
00:31:15,630 --> 00:31:16,690
Aren't you coming?

700
00:31:23,030 --> 00:31:23,550
Guys.

701
00:31:24,670 --> 00:31:25,230
Please.

702
00:32:17,780 --> 00:32:21,460
[Good Fortune Throughout the Year]

703
00:32:23,950 --> 00:32:25,830
As I stay awake until midnight,

704
00:32:26,450 --> 00:32:28,980
I get up from the bed and play the lute.

705
00:32:30,380 --> 00:32:32,870
Through the curtains comes the bright moonlight;

706
00:32:32,870 --> 00:32:36,070
The gentle breeze is blowing at my suit.

707
00:32:36,860 --> 00:32:39,110
In the wilderness shrieks the solitary swan;

708
00:32:39,110 --> 00:32:41,350
In the northern woods screams the circling bird.

709
00:32:41,350 --> 00:32:43,350
What do I see while I pace up and down?

710
00:32:43,950 --> 00:32:46,790
Alone I'm sad for what I saw and heard.

711
00:32:48,510 --> 00:32:49,770
It's snowing heavily.

712
00:32:49,910 --> 00:32:51,540
The bright moon is nowhere to be seen.

713
00:32:51,540 --> 00:32:53,470
Ruan Sizong's poem "Meditations"

714
00:32:54,350 --> 00:32:55,610
isn't suitable, is it?

715
00:32:56,820 --> 00:32:58,350
Indeed, it's not suitable.

716
00:32:58,350 --> 00:33:00,400
But I like this poem.

717
00:33:00,660 --> 00:33:02,390
It's because it hasn't been given

718
00:33:02,390 --> 00:33:03,990
more implications.

719
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:05,640
The only thing it expresses

720
00:33:05,670 --> 00:33:06,590
is sadness.

721
00:33:06,830 --> 00:33:08,430
Just sadness.

722
00:33:08,770 --> 00:33:10,530
Why are you suddenly so sad?

723
00:33:12,390 --> 00:33:14,320
The scene just evoked my emotions.

724
00:33:16,550 --> 00:33:18,820
Facing the heavy snow,

725
00:33:19,010 --> 00:33:20,140
which poem would you like to use

726
00:33:20,140 --> 00:33:21,600
to express your feelings?

727
00:33:23,500 --> 00:33:24,830
I only think of one line.

728
00:33:27,680 --> 00:33:29,550
The rivers and mountains are vast;

729
00:33:29,550 --> 00:33:31,950
They're actually thousands of miles wide.

730
00:33:32,080 --> 00:33:34,670
Thousands of miles wide.

731
00:33:34,990 --> 00:33:38,070
After all, you were once the General of the Imperial Guards.

732
00:33:38,070 --> 00:33:39,830
Just like my master's

733
00:33:39,870 --> 00:33:41,600
expectations of you back then.

734
00:33:49,070 --> 00:33:49,870
Who's inside?

735
00:33:50,200 --> 00:33:50,800
Come out!

736
00:33:52,110 --> 00:33:52,820
Come out!

737
00:33:59,150 --> 00:33:59,950
What's going on?

738
00:33:59,950 --> 00:34:00,830
What happened?

739
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:07,130
Why are you yelling?

740
00:34:07,430 --> 00:34:08,690
There's no one inside.

741
00:34:09,190 --> 00:34:10,719
I clearly heard some noise.

742
00:34:10,909 --> 00:34:12,370
If there was no one inside,

743
00:34:12,550 --> 00:34:13,909
could it be a ghost?

744
00:34:15,150 --> 00:34:15,840
Nonsense.

745
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:18,260
There's only a god in the ancestral hall.

746
00:34:18,270 --> 00:34:18,989
A god?

747
00:34:19,830 --> 00:34:21,389
Can you let us take a look?

748
00:34:26,790 --> 00:34:27,790
It's late.

749
00:34:28,190 --> 00:34:29,630
If we disturb the god,

750
00:34:29,929 --> 00:34:31,530
aren't you afraid that it may

751
00:34:31,550 --> 00:34:33,280
take one of your lives tonight?

752
00:34:35,199 --> 00:34:37,730
Are those who take people's lives still gods?

753
00:34:40,280 --> 00:34:41,760
Please do us a favor.

754
00:34:46,070 --> 00:34:46,929
Alright, then.

755
00:34:48,710 --> 00:34:49,510
Open the door.

756
00:35:14,330 --> 00:35:15,540
This is a god?

757
00:35:16,760 --> 00:35:17,560
What god is it?

758
00:35:17,560 --> 00:35:18,690
I don't know either.

759
00:35:19,270 --> 00:35:20,800
But it's very efficacious.

760
00:35:20,910 --> 00:35:21,870
When it receives incense,

761
00:35:21,870 --> 00:35:23,530
everything's fine in the inn.

762
00:35:23,700 --> 00:35:25,410
But if we don't give it offerings,

763
00:35:25,410 --> 00:35:27,470
ghosts will haunt the place at night.

764
00:35:34,990 --> 00:35:36,670
It's such a strange god.

765
00:35:38,510 --> 00:35:40,150
I've never seen it before.

766
00:35:41,170 --> 00:35:41,800
Mi.

767
00:35:42,030 --> 00:35:43,710
Do... Do you know this god?

768
00:35:43,990 --> 00:35:45,230
Even if he knows the god,

769
00:35:45,230 --> 00:35:46,630
the god doesn't know him.

770
00:35:47,550 --> 00:35:48,480
Stop kowtowing.

771
00:35:48,590 --> 00:35:49,950
It's... It's so scary.

772
00:35:50,070 --> 00:35:50,670
Exactly.

773
00:35:51,110 --> 00:35:52,790
Worshiping the wrong god will bring trouble.

774
00:35:52,790 --> 00:35:53,510
Go away.

775
00:35:53,950 --> 00:35:56,550
Don't disturb me while I'm worshiping the god.

776
00:35:56,990 --> 00:35:58,870
Every time after worshiping the god,

777
00:35:58,870 --> 00:36:00,710
I have to dust off the god.

778
00:36:20,750 --> 00:36:21,750
It's so cold here.

779
00:36:21,750 --> 00:36:22,550
Let's go back.

780
00:36:27,990 --> 00:36:29,100
Seeing this god today,

781
00:36:29,100 --> 00:36:30,430
I feel it's very mighty.

782
00:36:30,830 --> 00:36:32,550
I want to serve here all night

783
00:36:32,670 --> 00:36:34,490
in order to be blessed with safety in the future.

784
00:36:34,490 --> 00:36:35,030
No.

785
00:36:52,990 --> 00:36:54,030
Get him a blanket.

786
00:37:47,790 --> 00:37:48,400
Hermit.

787
00:37:49,190 --> 00:37:49,990
A toast to you.

788
00:37:51,790 --> 00:37:52,250
Cheers.

789
00:37:52,870 --> 00:37:53,910
Landlady.

790
00:37:54,840 --> 00:37:55,990
There're so many people here.

791
00:37:55,990 --> 00:37:56,870
You don't toast us.

792
00:37:56,870 --> 00:37:58,750
Why do you only toast him?

793
00:37:59,630 --> 00:38:01,350
I toast whomever I want.

794
00:38:01,750 --> 00:38:03,280
It's none of your business.

795
00:38:03,780 --> 00:38:04,620
Get lost.

796
00:38:08,830 --> 00:38:09,830
How rude of you!

797
00:38:11,040 --> 00:38:12,720
Not only did you not toast us,

798
00:38:12,900 --> 00:38:13,960
you also cursed me.

799
00:38:14,420 --> 00:38:15,540
When you cursed me before,

800
00:38:15,540 --> 00:38:16,420
I did nothing.

801
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:18,150
Now I have so many friends

802
00:38:18,150 --> 00:38:18,800
here.

803
00:38:19,120 --> 00:38:20,190
We're staying at your superior rooms

804
00:38:20,190 --> 00:38:21,680
and having your food and drink.

805
00:38:21,680 --> 00:38:23,310
You've already earned our silver ingots.

806
00:38:23,310 --> 00:38:23,750
You...

807
00:38:23,990 --> 00:38:25,120
You still cursed me.

808
00:38:25,230 --> 00:38:26,360
I'm old.

809
00:38:26,510 --> 00:38:27,910
Should I be cursed by you?

810
00:38:28,280 --> 00:38:30,350
You're taking advantage of your old age, right?

811
00:38:30,350 --> 00:38:31,270
Fine.

812
00:38:31,530 --> 00:38:32,860
After I toast Hermit,

813
00:38:33,230 --> 00:38:34,510
I'll toast you.

814
00:38:35,950 --> 00:38:36,580
Hermit.

815
00:38:38,950 --> 00:38:40,350
Landlady, thanks again.

816
00:38:54,960 --> 00:38:55,820
It's your turn.

817
00:39:13,030 --> 00:39:14,490
Drinking alone is boring.

818
00:39:15,430 --> 00:39:17,560
Why don't we play something exciting?

819
00:39:19,270 --> 00:39:20,200
How?

820
00:39:22,300 --> 00:39:23,900
How about the Tokhara Knife?

821
00:39:31,680 --> 00:39:32,610
This... This...

822
00:39:32,710 --> 00:39:35,060
This thing is too dangerous. I won't play.

823
00:39:35,120 --> 00:39:36,380
You don't dare to play?

824
00:39:36,700 --> 00:39:38,560
It's not that I don't dare to play.

825
00:39:39,030 --> 00:39:41,470
I still want to drink for a hundred years.

826
00:39:42,670 --> 00:39:43,310
Then

827
00:39:43,710 --> 00:39:45,430
it's not me who don't toast you.

828
00:39:45,430 --> 00:39:47,690
It's you who're not worth being toasted.

829
00:39:48,760 --> 00:39:49,260
Fed.

830
00:39:49,550 --> 00:39:50,170
Enough.

831
00:39:50,710 --> 00:39:51,230
Drink.

832
00:39:51,910 --> 00:39:52,340
Here.

833
00:39:54,960 --> 00:39:56,500
The blade of this dagger

834
00:39:56,940 --> 00:39:58,790
is usually retracted in the handle.

835
00:39:58,790 --> 00:40:00,990
There're nine gems around this circle.

836
00:40:01,500 --> 00:40:03,300
Only when one of them is pressed

837
00:40:03,480 --> 00:40:04,860
will the blade come out.

838
00:40:05,960 --> 00:40:07,160
The rule of the game is

839
00:40:07,350 --> 00:40:08,790
that two people participate.

840
00:40:08,790 --> 00:40:10,020
One person turns the button

841
00:40:10,020 --> 00:40:11,110
and hands it to the other person.

842
00:40:11,110 --> 00:40:14,060
The other person places the knife in front of his chest

843
00:40:14,060 --> 00:40:15,990
and presses the button on the tail.

844
00:40:16,230 --> 00:40:17,750
If the blade doesn't come out,

845
00:40:17,750 --> 00:40:19,280
the one who turns the button

846
00:40:19,430 --> 00:40:21,220
will toast him with a bowl of alcohol.

847
00:40:21,220 --> 00:40:22,710
If the blade comes out,

848
00:40:24,110 --> 00:40:25,550
then everyone here

849
00:40:26,190 --> 00:40:27,990
will toast him a bowl of alcohol.

850
00:40:40,330 --> 00:40:42,060
When you showed your unique skill,

851
00:40:42,060 --> 00:40:43,520
you looked quite valiant.

852
00:40:43,940 --> 00:40:44,740
Let's play it.

853
00:40:50,220 --> 00:40:51,200
I've heard about

854
00:40:51,800 --> 00:40:53,260
the Tokhara Knife before.

855
00:40:53,710 --> 00:40:55,110
It was once popular in the Western Region

856
00:40:55,110 --> 00:40:57,110
but was banned early in our country.

857
00:40:57,150 --> 00:40:59,390
I'll never participate.

858
00:41:01,810 --> 00:41:04,590
So you're just a good-looking but useless man.

859
00:41:05,270 --> 00:41:05,790
You...

860
00:41:09,670 --> 00:41:10,350
Forget it.

861
00:41:12,160 --> 00:41:12,830
Swordsman.

862
00:41:14,600 --> 00:41:16,480
You look scary with this sword.

863
00:41:16,890 --> 00:41:19,150
You pretend not to hear me at this moment.

864
00:41:20,400 --> 00:41:22,870
I didn't expect that on this snowy night,

865
00:41:23,550 --> 00:41:24,690
no one in the Mo's Inn

866
00:41:24,710 --> 00:41:26,660
has guts.

867
00:41:27,350 --> 00:41:28,080
I'll play it.

868
00:41:30,760 --> 00:41:32,090
But I want to add a bet.

869
00:41:32,590 --> 00:41:34,990
The gold coin you just got.

870
00:41:37,990 --> 00:41:38,710
Okay.

